The Nigeria Customs Service Bill 2022, which is currently before the National Assembly, is proposing a new Minister of Customs, as against the Ministry of Finance, which currently oversees the functions of the agency.  “Furthermore, the Nigeria Customs Service is not under the Ministry of Finance in the draft bill as indicated in paragraph 3.0 (1-5) clause 8-(3)(a). It indicates that there is a new Minster of Customs to be appointed by the president.
 
“A minister who shall be appointed by the president shall be a retired officer not below the rank of Deputy Comptroller-General,” clause 8-( 3) of the minister’s appointment stated. 